The goal of this course is to provide students with a grasp of the fundamentals of computer architecture and organization. Computer performance, data kinds and representations, arithmetic operations, instruction execution, microprogrammable control memory, pipelining, memory, input/output, and instruction format are all covered in this course. By the time this course ends, the student ought to be able to comprehend the idea of an entire computer component and be aware of the state-of-the-art in computer hardware technology.
